item.description:
A resident has contacted me with regards to a litter problem on the A40:&#10;&#10;&quot;We discussed the huge accumulation of litter along the A40 on the Golden Valley heading from Cheltenham towards the Longlevens roundabout and I said I would endeavour to send you photos.&#10;&#10;I have taken two videos this morning but one is too large to send and the other (attached) doesn’t demonstrate the scale of the problem but hopefully it is enough for you to bring to the attention of County Highways. I am sure they will already be well aware.&#10;&#10;The litter really is a scourge on our neighbourhood and doesn’t reflect well on Cheltenham or Gloucester as it is often the first thing that visitors note as they drive into our town.&quot;&#10;&#10;The County Council has stated: &quot;This particular stretch of the A40 is actually the responsibility of National Highways not GCC Highways. If you contact them they should be able to deal with this for you.&#10;&#10;Best wishes Claire&#10;&#10;Claire Hanson Manager Stakeholder Management &amp; Engagement Highways Gloucestershire County Council&quot;
<br>Nearest road to the pin placed on the map (automatically generated by OpenStreetMap): A40, Churchdown, Tewkesbury
<br><a href='https://www.fixmystreet.com/report/9166412'>Report on FixMyStreet</a>
